# Guidance for Using the Official PostgreSQL Documentation

During the development of this project, the developer must use the official **PostgreSQL** documentation as the main source of technical reference.

The official documentation should be used to validate database configuration, SQL syntax, data types, indexes, constraints, transactions, roles, permissions, performance optimization, backup strategies, replication, security practices, and other PostgreSQL-related resources.

## Recommendations for the Developer

- Consult the official PostgreSQL documentation whenever there are questions about database behavior or implementation.
- Prioritize the best practices recommended by the official PostgreSQL documentation.
- Avoid implementing database solutions based only on random examples found on the internet.
- Check whether the features being used are compatible with the PostgreSQL version adopted in the project.
- Use the documentation as a reference for technical decisions related to schema design, queries, indexing, and performance.
- Validate database changes carefully before applying them to production environments.

## Objective

Ensure that the project is developed following best practices, updated standards, and officially supported PostgreSQL resources.

[Consult the official PostgreSQL documentation during the development of the project:](https://www.postgresql.org/docs/)